[2] Diarrhea - Yemen: (Hodeidah)
Date: Sun 21 Oct 2007
Source: News Yemen [edited]
<http://www.newsyemen.net/en/view_news.asp?sub_no=3_2007_10_21_6930>


Tens of people in the districts of al-Dhoha, al-Zaidia, al-Qanawis,
al-Zahra, and al-Lohaiya of Hodeidah have been plagued with diarrhea,
but no deaths registered by the districts public health offices, a
medical source said.

The reason of diarrhea refers to [perhaps - Mod.LL] changes in the
digestive system as the time of meals changed after the holy month of
fasting, Ramadan, the source told NewsYemen. The source did not offer
definite number of plagued people in infected areas, but said that
field teams have visited the affected areas, which have diarrhea
infections every year, according to the source.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of Yemen can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/yemen.pdf>.
Hodeidah refers to extreme western Yemen bordering the Red Sea. - Mod.LL]

