[3] Diarrhea, fatal - Nepal: (Midwestern)
Date: Sun 21 Oct 2007
Source: All Headline News [edited]
<http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7008897935>


A diarrhea outbreak in Nepal has led to 23 deaths as of Sat 20 Oct
2007, and brought the number of infected to 500 since the outbreak
began. According to Dhaulaguwa Village Development Committee (VDC) in
Kalikot the outbreak has particularly and severely affected this
impoverished district. Dysentery broke out after the Saptari district
was under floodwater for several months.

Because of the alarm the disease had brought, a medical team composed
of 7 members, including the chief of the Department of Epidemiology
and Transferable Diseases, Laxmi Bikram Thapa, flew into the region.

According to Himalayan Times, the disease had crossed 19 districts
including Madhepura, Bamangamapatti, Rupnagar, Odraha, Haripur,
Bathnaha, Mahdewa, and Madhavpur.

[Byline: Cherry Mario]

--
